Area of a Field
Create a program that reads the length and width of a farmerâ€™s field from the user in
feet. Display the area of the field in acres.
Hint: There are 43,560 square feet in an acre.


length = int(input("enter the legth of fram"))
width = int(input("enter the width of farm"))
area = length * width
area_in_acers = area * 43560
print("area of farm is ", area_in_acers, "acers")
